OL,3,CPlanning inspector backs council in
OL,4,Clisted building banners row
OL,6,FBut, 17 months on, the government's
OL,7,Fplanning inspector has now dismissed
OL,8,Fthe appeal, according to the Local
OL,9,FDemocracy Reporting Service.
OL,11,FIn her judgement, inspector Elizabeth
OL,12,FPleasant questioned claims that the
OL,13,Fbanners were "temporary", pointing out
OL,14,Fthey had been in place since 2021.
OL,16,FShe said: "I appreciate the
OL,17,Fappellant's desire to protect the
OL,18,Fbuilding from vandalism, and to seek
OL,19,Fto demonstrate that the building
OL,20,Fcontinues to be in active use.
